name: within basins
description: A depression of the sea floor more or less equidimensional in form and of very variable extent

name: within guyots
description: An undersea mountain having a comparatively smooth flat top. Also called a table mount

name: within hills
description: Medium relief  (differences 250-1000 m within 5-10 km range) on land, tending to divergent form

name: within hollows
description: Low relief  (differences 30-250 m within 5-10 km range) on land, tending to convergent form

name: within mountains
description: High relief (differences > 1000 m within 5-10 km range) on land

name: (inapplicable)
description: None of the codes in the table are applicable in the context of this particular station/platform.

name: within plains
description: Very low relief  (differences <30 m within 5-10 km range) on land

name: within ridges
description: A long, narrow elevation with steep sides; or: A long, narrow elevation often separating ocean basins; or: The major oceanic mountain systems of global extent

name: within rises
description: Low relief (differences 30-250 m within 5-10 km range) on land, tending to divergent form

name: within sea mounts
description: An isolated or comparatively isolated elevation rising 1 000 meters or more from the sea floor and of limited extent across the summit

name: within trenches
description: A long, narrow and deep depression of the sea floor with relatively steep sides

name: within valleys
description: Medium relief (differences 250-1000 m within 5-10 km range) on land, tending to convergent form
